be.belgium.eid.objects
Class IDData

java.lang.Object
  be.belgium.eid.objects.IDData
All Implemented Interfaces:
SmartCardReadable
public class IDData
extends java.lang.Object
implements SmartCardReadable

The IDData class represents the ID data of a certain beID card. This data includes the personal information of the card holder such as the name, first name, municipality, birth information, ... . This data also includes information about the beID card itself such as the begin and end of the validity, the chip number of the card and the card number, ... .

Version:
1.0.0 07 Dec 2007
Author:
Kristof Overdulve

Initializes the IDData object with the given data.

Parameters:
cardNumber - is the card number of the ID
chipNumber - is the chip number of the ID
validFrom - is the date from when the ID is valid (must be before the validTo input)
validTo - is the date to when the ID is valid (must be after the validFrom input)
municipality - is the municipality where the holder of the ID lives
nationalNumber - is the national number
name - is the (last) name of the holder of the ID
firstname1 - is the 1st firstname of the holder of the ID
firstname3 - is the 3rd firstname of the holder of the ID
nationality - is the nationality of the holder of the ID
birthPlace - is the birth place of the holder of the ID
birthDate - is the birth date of the holder of the ID (must be a date in the past)
sex - is the sex of the holder of the ID (M/F)
nobleCondition - is the noble condition of the holder of the ID, this can be empty
documentType - is the type of document of the ID
isWhiteCane - indicates whether the holder of the ID is white cane (blind of very ill sighted)
isYellowCane - indicates whether the holder of the ID is yellow cane (partially sighted)
isExtendedMinority - indicates whether the holder of the ID is an extended minority
bs - is the hash of the photo of the holder of the ID

Parses the given stream of characters into a valid IDData object

Returns:
a fully initialized IDData object
Throws:
TagNotFoundException - indicates that some of the data hasn't been read in a proper format. If this occurs often, the ID card may be invalid
